  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-05/D3 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Synthetic adversarial sample embedding W-AR-05 (comparator absence) triggered via an inline validation result that omits comparedAgainst, combined with a D3 undercutting inference-method mismatch in which the experimental comparator dataset derives from a ventricular assist device (VAD) operating regime rather than the CPB flow-speed envelope declared in the COU.",
