      "rationale": "NIH is the established regulatory QoI for pump-induced hemolysis per FDA guidance. Shear stress and blood residence time are extracted as supporting QoIs to interpret mechanistic contributors to worst-case conditions. QoI relevance is well-established in the literature and accepted at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
