      "rationale": "The Lacasse et al. (2019) experiments used a magnetically levitated centrifugal pump in a cardiac-assist configuration. While the pump geometry and flow physics are closely related to the FDA generic centrifugal pump, the experimental dataset was collected under ventricular assist device (VAD) operating conditions (higher flow rates and extended duty cycles) rather than the CPB short-duration, lower-flow-rate envelope specified in the COU. The validation narrative treats this as a minor difference in operating regime, consistent with accepted practice for benchmark comparisons at MRL 2, and does not flag the VAD-to-CPB extrapolation as a limitation requiring additional qualification."
